Super Bowl Half-time Show.

15:15.760 --> 15:19.810
Wow. At last,
my pathetic little
life has a meaning.

15:19.960 --> 15:20.961
(CHUCKLES)

15:21.040 --> 15:23.441
You suckers,
I would've done it for free.

15:23.520 --> 15:24.931
Fine. Do it for free.

15:25.000 --> 15:27.128
Damn it.
Well, I'll still do it.

15:27.520 --> 15:30.410
(CHUCKLES) Suckers.
I would've paid you.

15:30.480 --> 15:31.686
Fine. Pay us.

15:32.000 --> 15:33.889
Oh, damn it.
Will you take a check?

15:33.960 --> 15:35.371
No.
Damn it.

15:38.680 --> 15:40.125
Mmm-hmm.

15:44.240 --> 15:46.561
ANNOUNCER: <i>The Super Bowl
Half-time Show.</i>

15:46.640 --> 15:49.246
<i>From its humble origins
in Super Bowl</i> I...

15:49.400 --> 15:51.721
(TROMBONE PLAYING)

15:51.800 --> 15:56.886
<i>...to the marriage of
Pac-Man and Ms. Pac-Man
in Super Bowl XVI.</i>

15:57.040 --> 16:00.522
<i>I now pronounce
you Pac-Man and wife.</i>

16:00.720 --> 16:04.247
<i>(SINGING) Let's get physical,
physical</i>

16:04.560 --> 16:07.211
<i>I wanna get physical</i>

16:07.520 --> 16:09.648
<i>Let's get into physical</i>

16:09.800 --> 16:14.169
(TURNS OFF TV)
Oh, every single Super Bowl
Half-time Show has been great.

16:14.240 --> 16:15.890
Oh, Homie, don't worry.

16:15.960 --> 16:18.088
I'm sure you'll come
up with a great idea.

16:18.240 --> 16:21.847
I don't know.
It's a lot of pressure.
(LAUGHS NERVOUSLY)

16:22.000 --> 16:25.163
Do many people
watch the Super Bowl?

16:25.240 --> 16:26.810
Billions.
Oh.

16:27.040 --> 16:28.166
(GUITAR PLAYING)

16:28.880 --> 16:30.370
(ELEPHANT TRUMPETING)

16:31.600 --> 16:34.843
We're ready for
rehearsal, Mr. Simpson.
So what do we do?

16:34.920 --> 16:37.321
(MEGAPHONE SWITCHES ON)
<i>Ah...</i>

16:38.200 --> 16:39.804
<i>Uh...</i>

16:39.880 --> 16:42.042
Oh, man, I have no
idea what I'm doing.

16:44.520 --> 16:46.522
I wonder if other Super Bowl
producers waited till

16:46.600 --> 16:50.241
3:00 in the morning
the night before to plan
their half-time shows.

16:51.720 --> 16:52.721
(TIRES SCREECHING)

16:52.800 --> 16:53.801
<i>A church.</i>

16:53.880 --> 16:57.202
Maybe the homeless people
sleeping on the floor
will have some ideas.

16:58.600 --> 16:59.840
Flanders?

17:00.000 --> 17:02.685
Well, I guess you've got
some late night problems, too.

17:02.760 --> 17:04.204
Yeah. I made a great film.

17:04.280 --> 17:06.123
But I'm having trouble
getting it out there.

17:06.280 --> 17:08.328
I'm like Michael Moore,
except I'm skinny,

17:08.400 --> 17:10.448
myjeans are washed,
and God loves me.

17:10.640 --> 17:13.530
(SIGHS) I just wish
I could find some way
to spread my message.

17:13.599 --> 17:15.204
Have you tried checking
the oil filter?

17:15.319 --> 17:16.685
Are you even listening to me?

17:16.800 --> 17:19.609
Sure. I'd be happy to
tell you my problem.

17:19.680 --> 17:21.808
I've got a venue
the whole world
will be watching

17:21.880 --> 17:23.369
and nothing to fill it with.

17:23.440 --> 17:24.487
Wait a minute.

17:24.560 --> 17:26.642
You've got a medium,
and I've got a message.

17:26.720 --> 17:28.643
Maybe God brought us
together for a reason.

17:28.840 --> 17:33.687
Yeah. You help me and I,
in turn, am helped by you.

17:35.000 --> 17:36.047
ANNOUNCER: <i>And so,
ladies and gentlemen,</i>

17:36.120 --> 17:40.648
<i>we have come to the start
of Super Bowl X-X-X-I-X.</i>

17:40.840 --> 17:44.845
<i>This brand new $300 million
stadium was completed
just one short week ago.</i>

17:45.160 --> 17:47.401
And it's scheduled
for demolition
early next month.

17:47.480 --> 17:49.721
America's priorities
are a joke. Now,

17:49.800 --> 17:51.006
<i>Here's the kickoff.</i>

17:51.080 --> 17:53.970
Wow. All these people
are gonna see Dad's show.

17:54.920 --> 17:56.922
Oh, I paid $1,000
for this seat.

17:57.000 --> 17:59.810
And I can't even see the game.
Just poke through.

18:01.160 --> 18:02.207
(SLURPS)
Hmm.

18:03.000 --> 18:04.001
(CROWD CHEERING)

18:04.080 --> 18:05.081
(GUNSHOT)

18:05.160 --> 18:06.605
ANNOUNCER: <i>And that's the gun.</i>

18:06.680 --> 18:10.924
<i>We head into half-time
with the thrilling
score of 55 to 6.</i>

18:11.080 --> 18:12.764
But don't stop watching
in the second half.

18:12.840 --> 18:13.887
Points count double.

18:13.960 --> 18:17.407
And now, the eagerly awaited
Super Bowl Half-time Show.

18:17.520 --> 18:21.206
Sponsored by
the new Ford pick-ups,
Citibank, and Moe's Tavern.

18:21.360 --> 18:22.486
How could you afford this?

18:22.560 --> 18:24.324
I hustled a lot of pool.

18:24.400 --> 18:25.890
Hey, you want to play?

18:26.200 --> 18:29.329
I gotta warn ya.
I ain't that good. (LAUGHS)

18:29.400 --> 18:30.526
All right.

18:31.440 --> 18:32.441
Sucker.

18:32.520 --> 18:33.965
(GRUNTS)

18:34.040 --> 18:35.326
Who's the sucker now? Huh?

18:38.560 --> 18:42.121
Time for Homer's
half-time show.
Get ready, Frank.

18:42.200 --> 18:44.851
Frank went to
the men's room.
I'm Joe.

18:45.200 --> 18:49.683
HOMER: <i>We now take you
back through the ages
to</i> a <i>time before TV,</i>

18:49.760 --> 18:53.003
<i>before cowboys,
before dinosaurs.</i>

18:53.080 --> 18:55.401
<i>The time of the Bible.</i>

18:57.920 --> 19:01.242
<i>The children of God
once lived according to
their father's laws.</i>

19:01.320 --> 19:04.290
<i>But then
a shadow of wickedness
fell across the land</i>

19:04.360 --> 19:07.682
<i>as represented by this
cloud of white pesticide.</i>

19:08.000 --> 19:09.889
(ALL COUGHING)

19:10.960 --> 19:14.407
<i>But there was one
righteous man, Noah.</i>

19:15.240 --> 19:19.848
<i>Oh, mighty God, send a flood
to destroy this wickedness.</i>

19:27.360 --> 19:29.328
Hey, you guys think
Homer's mad at me?

19:29.400 --> 19:31.926
I waved at him in
the parking lot and
he stared right through me.

19:32.080 --> 19:34.242
I left the People's
Republic for this?

19:34.720 --> 19:36.882
Yo, Michelle,
you got a boyfriend?

19:36.960 --> 19:38.041
Not in here, I don't.

19:38.960 --> 19:42.760
<i>After 40 days and 40 nights,
the rain stopped.</i>

19:42.840 --> 19:45.684
<i>And Noah set
forth a single dove.</i>

19:45.840 --> 19:46.841
(WHIMPERS)

19:49.520 --> 19:51.841
(WHIMPERING CONTINUES)

19:57.280 --> 19:59.931
So God blessed
Noah and his sons.
And said to them,

20:00.000 --> 20:03.721
"Never again
shall there be a flood
to destroy the earth.

20:03.800 --> 20:06.041
"I set my rainbow
in the cloud.

20:06.120 --> 20:11.331
"And it shall be a sign
of the covenant between
God and man." Thank you.

20:14.640 --> 20:16.051
(SPLASHING)

20:17.160 --> 20:18.810
(CROWD BOOING)

20:22.320 --> 20:25.051
<i>All over America today,
viewers were outraged</i>

20:25.160 --> 20:29.085
<i>by the Super Bowl Half-time
Show's blatant display
of religion and decency.</i>

20:29.240 --> 20:31.641
<i>You try to raise your kids
as secular humanists</i>

20:31.720 --> 20:34.849
<i>But these showbiz types
keep shoving religion
down our throats.</i>

20:34.960 --> 20:37.611
<i>Mommy,
why wasn't I baptized?</i>

20:37.680 --> 20:39.523
You see? You see?

20:39.680 --> 20:42.126
I thought America
was hungry for meaning.

20:42.200 --> 20:46.489
I should've just sent
a crocodile into space
like I originally planned.

20:46.920 --> 20:47.921
Oh.

20:48.360 --> 20:51.523
Homie, I think you did great.
And to celebrate,

20:51.600 --> 20:54.524
I made omelets from the eggs
people threw at our house.

20:54.800 --> 20:56.404
Dig in, everybody.

20:57.240 --> 21:00.084
Omelets for dinner?
This is the best
day of my life.

21:00.160 --> 21:03.289
Really? Didn't you just sign
a $90 million contract?

21:03.360 --> 21:04.691
That was a good day, too.

21:10.360 --> 21:13.125
HOMER: Welcome to
the Homer Simpson
Showboating Academy.

21:13.360 --> 21:16.250
Today we're working on
poor sportsmanship.

21:16.520 --> 21:18.409
But I like to stand
for good sportsmanship.

21:18.520 --> 21:20.124
Quiet, you.
Yes, sir.

